headline: Why Google's co-founders and Peter Thiel are exiting California
summary: Big Tech elites, like Alphabet's (GOOG, GOOGL) Google co-founders Sergey Brin and Larry Page and Palantir's (PLTR) Peter Thiel, are hauling out of California to escape the state's billionaire tax act, which entails a one-time 5% tax on their wealth. If approved, the tax could affect individuals who were California residents at the year's start. Tusk Venture Partners founder and CEO Bradley Tusk outlines what the shift out of California signals about taxation and the sociopolitical dynamics at play.
